  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in the kazan cauldron over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until it is translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger and cook for an additional 1 minute.",
    "Add the lamb and cook until it is browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the pomegranate molasses, cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Add 2 cups of water to the cauldron and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 2 hours, or until the lamb is tender.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with fresh herbs, if desired."
